Football Club Matera is an Italian association football club located in Matera, Basilicata. Currently it plays in Terza Categoria Matera. The club was founded in 1930. Matera has been as high as Serie B, playing in the second division for one season in 1979/1980 during the presidency of senator Francesco Salerno. It won the 200910 Coppa Italia Serie D and the promotion playoffs in 2009-10 Serie D, and was admitted to 2010-11 Lega Pro Seconda Divisione where it ranks 7th.[1] In summer 2011, it does not appeal against the exclusion of Covisoc and relegated to Terza Categoria. Its colors are white and blue.
